    "description": "Tools and tutorial on practical ray tracing for microscopy.\n\nThis code aims to provide a simple ray tracing module for calculating various properties of optical paths (object, image, aperture stops, field stops). It makes use of ABCD matrices and does not consider aberrations (spherical or chromatic). Since it uses the ABCD formalism (or Ray matrices, or Gauss matrices) it can perform tracing of rays and gaussian laser beams.",
